---
import '../styles/globals.css';
import '@fontsource-variable/inter/wght.css';
import interWoff2 from '@fontsource-variable/inter/files/inter-latin-wght-normal.woff2?url';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — Nerio – Conversation Insights</title>
  <meta name="robots" content="index,follow" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" href={interWoff2} crossorigin />
  <style>
    :root { --max: 880px; }
    body { font-family: 'Inter Variable', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.55; margin: 0; color: #111; background: #fff; }
    header, main, footer { max-width: var(--max); margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px; }
    header { padding-top: 40px; }
    h1 { font-size: 28px; margin: 0 0 8px; }
    h2 { font-size: 18px; margin: 28px 0 10px; }
    h3 { font-size: 16px; margin: 20px 0 8px; }
    p, li { font-size: 15px; }
    ul { padding-left: 20px; }
    .meta { color: #444; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 6px; }
    .box { background: #f6f7f8; border: 1px solid #e7e7e7; border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 16px; }
    a { color: inherit; }
    footer { color: #555; font-size: 13px; padding-bottom: 44px; }
    code { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 13px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="meta">
      Application: <strong>Nerio – Conversation Insights</strong><br/>
      Service Provider: <strong>Sandi Peklarić</strong><br/>
      Effective date: <strong>2026-01-01</strong>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="box">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Nerio – Conversation Insights</strong> (the "Application") collects, uses,
        and shares information when you use the Application. The Application is provided by <strong>Sandi Peklarić</strong>
        (the "Service Provider").
      </p>
      <p>
        By using the Application, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No accounts:</strong> the Application does not require you to create an account.</li>
      <li><strong>User content processing:</strong> conversation content you provide is processed to generate insights and is not stored by the Service Provider beyond what is necessary to complete processing.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> the Application uses Amplitude to understand usage and improve the Application.</li>
      <li><strong>Security & fraud prevention:</strong> the Application uses Firebase App Check to help protect the Application and prevent abuse.</li>
      <li><strong>No marketing emails:</strong> the Service Provider does not send marketing or promotional emails.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>2.1 Information you provide (User Content)</h3>
    <p>
      The Application allows you to provide conversation text (for example, messages or chat transcripts) so the Application can generate insights.
      This content is processed to provide the requested functionality. The Service Provider does not require an account to use the Application.
    </p>

    <h3>2.2 Purchase and subscription information</h3>
    <p>
      If you purchase a subscription, Apple processes the payment. The Service Provider may receive information such as purchase status
      (for example, whether a subscription is active) to provide access to subscribed features. The Service Provider does not receive
      your full payment card details.
    </p>

    <h3>2.3 Usage data and device identifiers</h3>
    <p>
      The Application may collect certain information automatically, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Usage data</strong> (e.g., app interactions, screens viewed, feature usage, session duration, performance events)</li>
      <li><strong>Device identifiers</strong> (e.g., device ID or other identifiers used for analytics, diagnostics, and fraud prevention)</li>
      <li><strong>Diagnostics</strong> (e.g., crash logs, error logs, and performance metrics)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>The Service Provider uses information for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>To operate the Application and provide its features (including generating insights from user-provided content)</li>
      <li>To process and manage subscription access (e.g., verifying an active subscription)</li>
      <li>To improve the Application's performance, reliability, and user experience</li>
      <li>To protect the Application against abuse, fraud, and unauthorized access</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests and communicate service-related notices</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Use of Artificial Intelligence</h2>
    <p>
      The Application uses artificial intelligence technologies to analyze user-provided content and generate insights.
      User content is processed only to provide the functionality you request. The Service Provider does not use your content
      to identify you and does not use it for marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>
      The Service Provider does not sell your personal information. The Service Provider may share information only in the following cases:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Service providers:</strong> with third-party vendors that help operate the Application (for example, analytics and security services),
        subject to their respective policies and contractual protections.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legal and safety:</strong> if required to comply with applicable law, regulation, legal process, or governmental request,
        or to protect the rights, property, or safety of users or the Service Provider.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Business changes:</strong> in connection with a merger, acquisition, reorganization, or sale of assets, in which case
        information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      The Application uses the following third-party services:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Amplitude (analytics):</strong> used to understand how the Application is used and to improve features and performance.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Firebase App Check (security / abuse prevention):</strong> used to help protect backend resources and reduce abusive traffic.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Apple In-App Purchase / StoreKit (payments):</strong> used to process subscription purchases and manage subscription status.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These services may collect information such as device identifiers, usage events, and diagnostics in accordance with their own privacy policies.
      You can review them here:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Amplitude Privacy Policy: <a href="https://amplitude.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://amplitude.com/privacy</a></li>
      <li>Google/Firebase Privacy Policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></li>
      <li>Apple Privacy: <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      The Service Provider retains information only for as long as necessary to provide the Application and comply with legal obligations.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>User-provided conversation content:</strong> processed to generate insights and not stored beyond what is necessary to complete processing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics and diagnostics data:</strong> may be retained for a limited period to understand usage and improve stability and performance.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Your Choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Opt-out of data collection:</strong> you can stop all collection by uninstalling the Application.</li>
      <li><strong>Data deletion requests:</strong> you may request deletion of any data the Service Provider controls by contacting the Service Provider (see Contact section below).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The Application is not directed to children under 13. The Service Provider does not knowingly collect personal information
      from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided personal information, contact the Service Provider to request deletion.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Security</h2>
    <p>
      The Service Provider uses reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect information.
      However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and the Service Provider cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      The Service Provider may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective date" at the top indicates when the latest
      changes took effect. Continued use of the Application after changes means you accept the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, contact:
      <br/><strong>Sandi Peklarić</strong>
      <br/>Email: <a href="mailto:sandi.peklaric@gmail.com">sandi.peklaric@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>
      Note: This Privacy Policy is provided for transparency to users and to support App Store review requirements. It does not create a lawyer-client relationship.
      If you need legal advice for your jurisdiction, consult a qualified attorney.
    </p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
